  "body": "https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/api/envoy/data/dns/v3/dns_table.proto#L62\r\nhas a validation stating that the DNS name length must be atleast 2 characters which seems very arbitrary. Consider a kubernetes pod (or even a local network). It is certainly possible to create services like a, b, c and they can all be resolved using the single character short names, within the k8s namespace, while cross namespace resolution uses a.<ns>, b.<ns>. Yes, it sounds weird but its possible theoretically.\r\n\r\ncc @abaptiste ",
